message.text:
<KANJI Quiz!>
Do you know the meaning of the Kanji "才"？ Choose the answer!
1.clothes 2. member 3. talent

“才” is read as “Sai（さい）” and besides the meaning above, it also means a counter for “Age”. Some of you may think “歳（さい）” is the official Kanji when counting age, and yes, you are right! Both kanji have same pronunciation “Sai” but originally different meanings and graphically unrelated. “才” is very common word now and taught around younger age as a replacement character of “歳”！

Kanji has so many ways to read...it is very interesting but tricky...Very hard to memorize, isn't it?

「才」の意味、わかりますか？
才は歳と同じ音で、年齢をあらわす時にも使われます。
漢字の読み方、たくさんあって大変ですよね。
http://www.anime-manga.jp/KanjiGame/School/

message.text:
Tomorrow, September 23rd, is another holiday in Japan! 
We call it "Shūbun no Hi" (秋分の日), or Autumnal Equinox Day!

 This is the very day the sun crosses the equator from the Northern to the Southern Hemisphere. Hence, from today and on, the nighttime will lengthen. 

During the days around Shūbun no Hi, we often eat Japanese traditional sweet rice cake covered with soybean jam. We call it "Ohagi"（おはぎ）, since it resembles the seasonal flower "Hagi"（はぎ）. 
From long time ago, the red color of the soybean jam is believed to protect you from evil spirits. 
Therefore, Ohagi is served as a sign of appreciation to the ancestors that protect us and the mountain gods that bring us rich harvest in autumn. 
If you have chance, why don't you try it!?

 9月23日は秋分の日!
 昼と夜の長さがほぼ同じになる日で、少しずつ夜が長くなっていきます。
 日本では、秋分の日の頃になると「おはぎ」を食べる風習があります。
 これは、昔からおはぎに使われるあんこの赤い色は悪いものを追い払うといわれており、私たちを守る「祖先」や豊作をもたらしてくれる「山の神」をうやまい感謝をあらわす物として食べられているんですよ。う～ん、食べたい！

message.text:
London, UK: September 24 [Special Talk] An Introduction to SAKE
英国・ロンドン：9/24 [トーク]日本酒の世界への招待 
http://www.jpf.org.uk/whatson.php#689

Did you know that October 1 is "Sake, or Nihonshu (日本酒） Day"?
There are 3 reasons:
(1)One of the main ingredients in sake is rice, and rice harvest finishes in autumn.
(2)There are many hands for brewing because the autumn-winter is agricultural off-season.
(3)Cool climate of autumn-winter is best for fermentation process of Sake.

It's also the best season to try Sake because Autumn is full of good seasonal food to go with it! It's "食欲の秋"（Shokuyoku-no-Aki, Autumn Appetite）, so why don't you try Sake today with good Autumn food?

FYI: If you want to try Sake, but can't drink or not good at drinking, you can taste Sake-like drink "Amazake"(甘酒）, a traditional sweet, low- or non-alcohol (depending on recipes) Japanese drink made from fermented rice, which is usually for New Year's celebration or summer as a nutrition drink:)))

10月1日は「日本酒の日」って知っていますか？

秋はお酒の原料となるお米がちょうど収穫されて、気候的にもとってお酒を醸造するには最適な季節だからだそうです。
秋は「食欲の秋」！お酒に合う旬の秋の味覚がたくさん！皆さん今日試してみては？
（お酒がだめという人には、ノンアルコールの「甘酒」もありますよ～。）
